{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"[G3 child-coverage audit — parent c81c plan-review fan-out epic; this child S2 (engine-wide caching via RunnerAgentStep) reviewed whole against the full sibling roster]\n\n4-bucket audit of the parent's acceptance/success criteria, mapping S2's contribution and cross-checking every absence against the roster (S1 0250, S3 ba7e, S4 98c6, S5 1762, S6 da34):\n\n- \"caching applied across plan-review AND all workflow agent steps\" (success criterion) — FULLY covered HERE for the engine-wide leg. S1 explicitly fences out RunnerAgentStep (\"Out: engine RunnerAgentStep caching (S2)\"), so S2 is the SOLE sibling covering verify/decide/coach/grounding + completion-verification + code-review caching. Clean producer→consumer split with S1 (S1 owns the runner cache mechanism; S2 owns RunnerAgentStep prefix-wiring + the stable-vs-volatile prompt-model convention).\n- \"materially lower token cost (cache reads non-zero)\" — PARTIAL here (S2 adds engine-step cache reads: AC `cache_read > 0` on repeats for verify/decide/coach + completion-verification + code-review). The plan-review container token win is S1's domain. Covered by roster.\n- \"8-child epic review completes in minutes (wall-clock)\" — STRUCTURAL/not-applicable here (S2 is engine-step caching, not the plan-review fan-out latency lever); wall-clock → sibling ba7e (S3). Covered by roster.\n- \"caching provider-safe: openai/gemini succeed unchanged\" — PARTIAL here, correctly: S2's AC carries \"unchanged on other providers\", extending S1's anthropic-gating to the engine steps. Mechanism owned by S1. Covered.\n- \"no fidelity regression / within offline-eval tolerance\" — covered HERE for the relocation risk S2 introduces: the single-pass G3-1 remediation added a FIDELITY-VERIFY AC for the 11 relocated gate prompts (esp. completion-verifier, which backs the mandatory close gate, + code-review) — no longer asserted. Epic-wide semantic eval → sibling da34 (S6). Covered.\n- \"make lint + suite pass\" — per-child portion covered here (AC: \"make lint + tests pass\").\n- \"all six child stories closed\" — aggregate/structural; not a single-child mapping.\n\nNo parent acceptance/success criterion is left uncovered by the union of children, and S2 introduces no parent-criterion it then leaves uncovered (the relocation-fidelity risk it creates is closed by its own G3-1 fidelity AC). G3: CLEAN — no findings for this pairing."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782578685908350001,"uuid":"768f66f9-4e78-48ae-a996-dc1e8fb0d665"}